```
If `damon_call_handle_inactive_ctx` removes the control and returns `-EINVAL`, then `damon_call` returns `-EINVAL`. The control is removed from the list, so no dangling pointer.
What if `damon_call_handle_inactive_ctx` finds that the control is already removed? Then it returns 0.

