The `commit_inputs` store will call `damon_lru_sort_commit_inputs_store`, which calls `damon_call(ctx, &control)`.
If this `damon_call` hits the race condition, the `commit_inputs` store thread blocks forever.
Since the control is left in `ctx->call_controls`, what happens when the user later does `echo Y > enabled`?
`damon_lru_sort_turn(true)` calls `damon_start(&ctx, 1, true)`, which creates a new `kdamond` thread!
